Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
highlight_pin_connection(25.10)                highlight_pin_connection(25.10)

Name
       highlight_pin_connection  - Highlights the full timing path or its seg-
       ment in the text format while generating the sign-off timing report

Syntax
       highlight_pin_connection

       [-help]

        -from_pin <pin>[-mode {wire_segment | whole_net | flight_line}]

        -to_pin <pin>[-with_arrow | -select_only]

        [-net_color_index <index_value >| -select_only]

       [-inst_color_index <index_value >| -select_only]

       Highlights the full timing path or its segment in the text format while
       generating the sign-off timing report. Use this command to quickly  de-
       bug the timing path (timing point information) used in the tool.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each highlight_pin_connection parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man highlight_pin_connection

       -from_pin <pin>
              Specifies the name of the starting pin or IO port  to  be  high-
              lighted.

       -inst_color_index <index_value>
              Specifies  the instance color index value (an integer value from
              1 to 64) for the specified timing path.

       -mode {wire_segment | whole_net | flight_line}
              Specifies the draw mode between the starting and ending pins.

       -net_color_index <index_value>
              Specifies the net color index value (an integer value from 1  to
              64) for the specified timing path.

       -select_only
              Selects only the specified path for highlighting.

       -to_pin <pin>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the  ending pin or IO port to be high-
              lighted.

       -with_arrow
              Specifies whether or not the connection is defined with  an  ar-
              row.

Example
       The  following command highlights a line drawn from the specified input
       pin to output pin while generating the sign-off timing report:

       highlight_pin_connection -from_pin ffa/Q -to_pin U7/A -mode flight_line

